summary: We are a Marvel family, not a DC family. It’s in your blood. You May disagree with Marvel sometimes, and occasionally you will...
text: We are a Marvel family, not a DC family. It’s in your blood. You May disagree with Marvel sometimes, and occasionally you will question their story decisions. That’s okay. You will meet people–fine people, DC people–and they will tempt you with engaging DC titles. Experiment. Read some Batman. We’ve all done it, But the siren song of the M.U. will bring you home when the time is right.
source:
Chelsea Cain: Man-Eaters #5

Written by a woman whose comics series was axed by Marvel, before publication, halfway into production. This is beyond gracious.

title: We Love Tony Stark Wednesday
body:
You know what? I am so down with the idea that all Tony used to listen to in the lab was a bunch of rock music like AC/DC and stuff until Peter came along. Like, at first, when Peter shyly asks for the first time if he could play some of his own music for the two of them to listen to in the lab, Tony grumbles a “sure”, but then it doesn’t take long for him to warm up to Peter’s music. 

So now, the two have made a playlist specifically for when they’re together in the lab that includes some of Tony’s classic rock songs along with some of Peter’s pop songs (some of them are rock as well, and Tony’s rather surprised by that, but just makes them bond even more) 

Occasionally, some of the Avengers might pop in to ask Tony something until they see a glorious moment between Tony and Peter. The two of them taking a break from fixing suits, and instead, dancing around, singing along to Bohemian Rhapsody at the top of their lungs and using wrenches as their microphones. 

It would usually be Clint, Sam or Rhodey who would end up video recording them doing so, so they could use it as blackmail one day.
